      "version": "",
      "Uid": null,
      "IsMRef": true,
      "Title": "GardaVettingSystem.Models.AccessCode",
      "Summary": "<p sourcefile=\"api/GardaVettingSystem.Models.AccessCode.yml\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"1\">Represents a time-limited access code generated by an applicant for a specific organisation.</p>\n<p>Access codes allow organisations to retrieve an applicant's vetting data without the applicant\nneeding to re-enter their information.</p>\n<p>Codes are designed to be revocable and time-limited\nin line with GDPR principles of integrity and confidentiality.</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "ManagedReference",
      "source_relative_path": "api/GardaVettingSystem.Models.Applicant.yml",
      "output": {
        ".html": {
          "relative_path": "api/GardaVettingSystem.Models.Applicant.html"
        }
      },
      "version": "",
      "Uid": null,
      "IsMRef": true,
      "Title": "GardaVettingSystem.Models.Applicant",
      "Summary": "<p sourcefile=\"api/GardaVettingSystem.Models.Applicant.yml\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"1\">Represents an applicant's personal profile in the Garda Vetting Data Reuse System.</p>\n<p>Each registered user can have one applicant profile, which stores personal information\nrequired for Garda vetting applications.</p>\n<p>The profile can be shared with organisations via generated access codes, \neliminating the need for repeated data entry.</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "ManagedReference",
      "source_relative_path": "api/GardaVettingSystem.Models.ApplicantAddress.yml",
      "output": {
        ".html": {
          "relative_path": "api/GardaVettingSystem.Models.ApplicantAddress.html"
        }
      },
      "version": "",
      "Uid": null,
      "IsMRef": true,
      "Title": "GardaVettingSystem.Models.ApplicantAddress",
      "Summary": "<p sourcefile=\"api/GardaVettingSystem.Models.ApplicantAddress.yml\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"1\">Represents a single address entry in an applicant's address history.</p>\n<p>An applicant can have multiple addresses covering different periods of residence.</p>\n<p>Address history is a standard requirement for Garda vetting applications.</p>\n"
    },
